I have a new friend who has just arrived at the Plane of Firiona Vie and he would like to join a guild.  I have looked at The List, but I am looking for some pretty specific qualities that are (understandably) not included.  This is what I am looking for or would like to create.  (I don't want to create a new guild, though, if one already exists that matches up.)  I like the server a lot, and the people I have met so far have been great.<br>
<br>
1) Strong emphasis on roleplaying in all settings (in guild chat and on forums -- ooc pretty much restricted to tells, emergencies, or specific forums.<br>
2) Good in alignment -- their purpose is to seek out and thwart evil.<br>
3) Allows all races with the assumption that people from &quot;evil&quot; stock have committed themselves to fighting for the cause of good.  (I have a Dark Elf on the &quot;Plane of Xegony&quot; who is good and believes the rest of his race to be misguided.)<br>
4) Allows creative license as far as background.  If a troll wants to claim to worship Tunare, I won't argue.  In other words, the game mechanics don't need to match with the roleplaying put forward by the players.<br>
5) Includes all levels of experience, low through 65.<br>
6) I can go either way on including all classes, but I have heard some good roleplaying reasons why necromancers are not evil.  I think the same could be done for SK's.<br>
7) I prefer a guild large enough so that there is diverse talent and so people can actually pursue goals and adventures together.<br>
<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  One that is friendly and gets along well -- primarily not whiney with a lot of in-fighting.  By Brells' Stout, I hate that. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
9) A fairly active message board/forums, to help keep people tied together.<br>
Thanks for your thoughts on this matter. <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.eqfaces.com/photos/mith6.jpg"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
